title: The Story Girl
creator: Lucy Maud Montgomery
description: Librivox recording of The Story Girl by Lucy Maud Montgomery. The Story Girl, by Anne of Green Gables author L.M. Montgomery, tells about the summer Felix and Beverly King visit their cousins in Carlise, Canada. Along with various cousins and other soon-to-be-friends, they meet their Sara Stanley, the Story Girl, a cousin who has a story for every situation. As the children pass they summer, they get into trouble, have adventures, listen to the Story Girl's enchanging tales, and then... get into a bit more trouble! (Summary by Heather Barnett) M4B audiobook of complete book For information about our readers, see our catalog page: http://librivox.org/the-story-girl-by-lucy-maud-montgomery/ For more free audiobooks, or to find out how you can volunteer, please visit librivox.org.
